by Valentine Z » Mon Nov 16, 2020 12:27 pm

The Soundgebede wrote:The Waisnorian currency -the Thaler- was introduced in 1992, and can be found in 4 different coin types and 7 different banknote types, going from $0.5 to $2,000. How a Thaler is pegged to USD (or NSD) I don't know.

I particularly found this bit interesting from the history section: Singapore was then under hold of the Sultan of Johore, under inflow from the Netherlands. The Sultan would, Raffles knew, never give over Singapore to the Anglo-Danes, but there was another way. The Sultan's brother -Tengku Hussein- would agree to let Anglo-Danes put tradeposts in Singapore if they helped him become Sultan there. With Anglo-Danish help, he was crowned Sultan in Singapore 1819, and while he held some weald at first, by the Fordrawing of 1824, he was all but sidelined.

If I am reading this right, it would seem that Singapore in this world was held by Johore (Johor, more or less), from the Dutch giving them an influx of people and capital (at least, I think that was what "under inflow" would mean in this context). It would be more or less close to the history of RL Singapore, so I was quite happy with that little bit. The deviation would be the fact that this seemed to have happened a little later, because around that year and timeframe, the British would have eventually taken over Singapore, and we became (part of) the British colony.

I can only wonder what would happen if Singapore was fully under control of the Anglo-Danes, or hell, if the Sultan managed to anticipate the Great Wars. Would certainly make for more interesting read, and if WW1-2 happened in your world, might change how Singapore might be shaped, or if it even went into the Japanese Occupation phase.

I particularly love this bit! Each Ravenelki wears a set of elaborately decorated black and red power armor, which is perhaps the most durable in serial production in the Empire, bested only in durability by the personal armor worn by Alexander Mercer himself. Their armor is powered by an experimental reactor which uses E-99 to power it, using a fusion of technology and magic. They can use these to access other dimensions, travel to places instantaneously, and then emerge there in our dimension with no time having passed.

Learning about the fact that technology and magic plays hand-in-hand in their world, and being able to travel to other dimensions without time being passed. Of course, the "no time having passed" would mean that it was only for the dimensional travel, so I was wondering if they could, in theory, pull a Narnia? Can they travel to Dimension B, spend maybe 4 days in there, and travel back to Dimension A with exactly 1 second being passed?
